DynamicScript - imperative script programming language with lambdas, dynamic typing, code templating and quotations.

1. Requirements
==================
WINDOWS
	.NET Framework 4.0 Client Profile

LINUX
	Mono 2.10.x

2. Building
==================
Clone GIT repository from GITHUB:
		git clone git://github.com/sakno/DynamicScript.git

WINDOWS
	1. Open Windows Command Line processor;
	2. Change the current directory to the 'csharp' directory;
		cd D:\git_repos\DynamicScript\csharp
	3. Specify output directory;
		SET OUTDIR=bin
	4. Execute 'make.cmd' command file;
		make.cmd %OUTDIR%
	5. Examine output directory.
LINUX
	1. Open Terminal;
	2. Change the current directory to the 'csharp' directory;
		cd ~/git_repos/DynamicScript/csharp
	3. Specify output directory;
		export OUTDIR=bin
	4. Specify path to the XBUILD tool;
		export XBUILD=/opt/mono/bin/xbuild
	5. Execute make.sh file;
		sh make.sh $OUTDIR;
	6. Examine output directory;

